The paper proposes a regularization framework for training neural networks for classification tasks with few training samples. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on classification tasks and proposes a regularization term, it is most likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) followed by computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
